  "original_title": "1,164 \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bcb\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 1,086 \u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b95 \u0ba8\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "1,086 suspects arrested in 1,164 fuel check round-up operations",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Police Media Spokesperson Senior Superintendent of Police Nihal Taldua said that 1,086 suspects have been arrested during the 1,164 fuel check round-up operations carried out so far in the country.",
        "He also said that 37,296 liters of petrol, 119,457 liters of diesel and 19,214 liters of kerosene have been seized in the said fuel inspection operation.",
        "The Police Media Spokesman further mentioned that some were illegally hoarding fuel to sell it at higher prices.",
        "He added that investigations into such incidents would continue and the police would be vigilant about all such incidents."
      ],
